                <h1>Discover the Iconic Ivy of Wrigley Field</h1>
                <p>Wrigley Field's ivy-covered outfield walls are iconic, making it one of baseball's most beloved stadiums. Planted in 1937, the ivy not only adds beauty but also influences gameplay, as balls can get lost in the greenery. This unique feature has become a symbol of the Chicago Cubs and a must-see for fans visiting the historic ballpark.</p>
